## 🛠 Step 15 — Admin Panel (Routes, Fees & Policies)

**Goal:** Give admins the ability to tweak platform behavior in real time — control fees, allowed/blocked bridges & DEXs, slippage presets, referral logic, and featured assets.

---

### 1) Core Features

* **Fee Control**

  * Change fee BPS per route type (e.g., stable swaps, volatile swaps, cross-chain swaps).
  * Different fees per chain if desired.
* **Route Policy Management**

  * Allow/block specific bridges & DEXs (from Step 7’s policy engine).
  * Set priority bridges per chain.
* **Slippage Defaults**

  * Set global and token-specific slippage.
* **Referral & Leaderboard Settings**

  * Adjust referral % payouts.
  * Toggle leaderboard visibility.
* **Featured Assets**

  * Pin specific token pairs on homepage or transfer UI.

---

### 2) DB Schema

Example Prisma additions:

```prisma
model AdminConfig {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  key         String   @unique
  value       Json
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt
}

model BlockedRoute {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  chainId     Int
  bridge      String
  dex         String?
  reason      String?
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
}
```

---

### 3) API Endpoints

* `GET /api/admin/config`
* `POST /api/admin/config` (auth-protected)
* `GET /api/admin/routes/blocked`
* `POST /api/admin/routes/block`
* `DELETE /api/admin/routes/block/:id`

Use JWT-based admin auth or connect to your wallet + on-chain signature verification.

---

### 4) Frontend (Next.js + Tailwind)

* Separate `/admin` route guarded by auth.
* Tabs: **Fees**, **Policies**, **Referrals**, **Assets**.
* Reuse UI components from user-facing site for consistency.

Example component:

```tsx
function FeeEditor({ current, onSave }) {
  const [fees, setFees] = useState(current);
  return (
    <div className="space-y-2">
      {Object.keys(fees).map(type => (
        <input
          key={type}
          value={fees[type]}
          onChange={e => setFees({...fees, [type]: Number(e.target.value)})}
          className="border p-2 rounded"
          placeholder={`${type} fee BPS`}
        />
      ))}
      <button onClick={() => onSave(fees)} className="bg-brand text-white px-3 py-1 rounded">
        Save
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

---

### 5) Integration

* Fetch config on app load to override default fee/slippage settings.
* On update, cache bust & refresh policy filters so user routes reflect new rules instantly.

